  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: software fault coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The solver pipeline is implemented as a multi-threaded RANS-based CFD code with a custom hemolysis post-processor written in Python; all validation runs reported nominal completion. One isolated convergence stall was observed in a preliminary mesh-sensitivity sweep and attributed to an overly coarse initial mesh; no further investigation of solver-level failure modes was undertaken. Dominant numerical fault modes — including floating-point NaN propagation in the power-law hemolysis kernel, race conditions in the parallel boundary-condition exchange, and edge-case crashes at zero-shear-rate cells — were not exercised during verification or validation activities.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "conformsToProfile_cou": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
